In America, home brewing beer has been slowly gaining in popularity since 1978 when federal laws concerning making beer at home changed. By 2013, it was finally legal to brew beer for your own use in every state. Like cooking, many brewers enjoy altering the different formulas, ingredients, and combinations. The Grape and Granary sells everything you need, from hops to extracts, to alter your recipes and brew a beer that is unique to you. The ability to experiment with the ingredients to create different beers is often incredibly enjoyable to many home brewers.
The Grape and Granary does not limit itself to beer and wine making equipment. They also serve the needs of several other pastimes. For those looking to explore other forms of fermentation, you can find everything you need to make sake (fermented rice), mead (fermented honey), and vinegar here, including books, PDFs, and supplies.
